review:
Doctor is very nice so sweet she is, i am planning to go very frequently i will make her my personal doctor.
I had gone there with my blood report i had low vitamin b12 and vitamin D i was freaking out but she calmly told me science of everything why what is happening and how is it happening how it can be cured she is so nice definitely recommend her.
She listens everything!! Explains everything
Good and experienced Doctor. Explained the possible causes of illness well. Suggested remedies and medicines that are not very costly.
ma'am's medicines have always helped usI have consulted her only for cough, the medicines she prescribed have worked. they are simple tablets. not heavy medication

review: very nice doctor! she explained me very well, why is she recommended the medicines she recommended. I will definitely recommend her.
She explained everything very well and also helped me with a good substitutary diet plan along with medicines.
Doctor is very friendly,  understands issue very patiently and advised you proper treatment, will not give unnecessary medicines, very good doctor

I visited this clinic and the doctor for the first time, and I was very satisfied with the overall experience. I had a bad throat and dry cough for the past few days, and it was getting worse, so I visited Dr. Meenakshi, and she not only prescribed me medicine but also asked me to follow certain home remedies. She also didn't give me a list of medications to pop like the other doctors. I highly recommend her, and I'm happy to have found a general physician for myself.

The doctor is very kind and patient. Unlike the doctors of today she listens to all your issues patiently and explains the treatment. She also recommends simple diet and lifestyle changes and gives appropriate high quality medicines , and  not the ones which have high MR margin.

She was patient and spoke softly. Listened to the issue and exppained what could be the problem. Slow approach to medicine. Didn't bombard me with too many medicines, recommended food and lifestyle change options and asked for a follow up (which is free within 7 days) to determine further course of action, if any. 
Her office staff were polite and helpful. I lost my phone sometime between leaving her office and going to the medicine store and they all, including the doctor, tried helping me track it. One of them found it. 
All in all, very good experience and would 100% recommend her.
reply_text: Thank you very much Aayati. It means a lot.
